Alchemy ranks up there with poison making.  Can be useful, but for the most part, it is just a very expensive hobby.

I was pretty psyched about being able to make EB potions.. until I discovered that 'magic potion' vendors sell EB pots for 10 pp, 5 gp.  That's less than it cost me to attempt!  Even more insulting is that the user does not have to have a fish scale on them to activate the vendor bought potion. (O.o)  The only advantage then to Shamanic EB potions is that you can  stack 5 or 10 doses.

There are some potions that only Shamans can make (to my knowledge) such as SoW, Shrink and ITU.  These are very useful!  A SoW potion is faster than Jboots, and that is a good thing (^.~)  

The only things I have been ever requested to make so far are: SoW, Shrink, ITU, and Damage Shield.

I like alchemy, its a neat thing,.. but the economy on it is (still) a bit messed up.   For the most part, the cost to make the potions for ingrediants alone far exceeds anyones interest in purchasing them. And that is ignoring a normal rate of return to compensate for the Shaman's time.  In alot of cases, there are other cheaper and sometimes less expendable ways to get the same effect.

On the other hand, I must also admit that alchemy has improved astoundingly since it was first introduced!  /cheer. 

